title: 820-00165 no power
message:
Check the MLB alone, withput LIO flex connected, nor other peripheral device.
Post PM_BATLOW_L, PM_RSMRST_L, PM_PWRBTN_L, PCH_DSWVRMEN, PM_DSW_PWRGD.
Trigger SMC_ONOFF_L and check for drop pulse at PM_PWRBTN_L.
If yes, then check for any pulse at PM_SLP_Sx_L signals at same time.

title: 820-00165 no power
message:
Looks like PCH issue.

"PM_SLP_S3_L : 1.753V"
This is very strange, because, PM_SLP_S5/4_L should appear first.
And even 1.7V is not good at all.

No pulse at all at PM_SLP_S5/4_L?

title: 820-00165 no power

title: 820-00165 no power
message:
PM_SLP_S3_L  (as all other PM_SLP_Sx_L signals) is pulled high inside PCH.
So bad PCH most likely.
Can still be a problem with U8180, or U1930; but not common...
